contentrichtext.text: {{Italic title prefixed|3}} '''USS ''Porpoise''''' has been the name of more than one United States navy ship, and may refer to: * {{USS|Porpoise|1820}}, a schooner built in 1820 and wrecked in 1833 * {{USS|Porpoise|1836}}, a brig in commission from 1836 to 1847, from 1848 to 1852, and from 1853 until lost in 1854 * {{USS|Porpoise|SS-7|}}, a submarine commission from 1903 to 1919, renamed USS ''A-6'' in 1911 * USS ''Porpoise'' (YFB-2047), steamer in commission from 1918 to 1930, originally named {{USS|Moosehead|ID-2047}} * {{USS|Porpoise|SS-172}}, a submarine in commission from 1935 to 1945 ;Also *A patrol vessel named {{USS|Porpoise|SP-4}} may have served ca. 1917-1919, but no records of her acquisition, commissioning, or service have been found {{Shipindex}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Porpoise}} [[Category:United States Navy ship names]]
